body:
When I tried with struct array like:

```
  typedef struct {
    rand int field_a;
    rand int field_b;
  } simple_struct_t;

  rand simple_struct_t struct_array[3];
```
  
  The result shows, field a is not assigned correctly(always 0) while only field_b is randomized.
  It happens the same if we have three members in struct, only the last one is correctly randomized.(Check the fig)
<img width="186" alt="r1" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/72c80564-4b72-4ad7-9c9b-a8fa2c033d55">

If we check the dumped json file, it shows like:
<img width="911" alt="r2" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/468e5367-d0c3-49a1-a0da-5a6542400950">

  The reason might be: in stmtsp of foreach node, only the last assign statement works.
  
  Currently I report this as an unsupported message with PR #5415
